la: Quid si nolo vel nullus fuerint? quis denique singularis Christiani? Non erit, opinor, legitimus Christianus nisi frater aut filius.
en: But if they wont come, or if you have none? What, Christians with no relatives? I suppose, a man is not a regular Christian unless he is a brother or a son.

la: propterea ergo magis quaero is Judaeus interficio quia non solus solvo sabbata sed et Patrem suus dico Deum aequalis sui facio Deo respondeo itaque Iesus et dico is
en: Hereupon therefore the Jews sought the more to kill him, because he did not only break the sabbath but also said God wa his Father, making himself equal to God.

la: nonne iste sum qui decipio filius Israhel ad suggestio Balaam et praevaricaris tu facio in Domino super pecco Phogor unde et percutio sum populus
en: Are not these they, that deceived the child of Israel by the counsel of Balaam, and made you transgress against the Lord by the sin of Phogor, for which also the people wa punished?

la: non addo ad verbum qui tu loquor neque aufero ex is custodio mandatum Domini Dei vester qui ego praecipio tu
en: You shall not add to the word that I speak to you, neither shall you take away from it: keep the commandment of the Lord your God which I command you.

la: ut recordor et confundaris et non sum tu ultra aperio os prae confusio tuus cum placo sum tu in omnis qui facio aio Dominus Deus
en: That thou mayest remember, and be confounded, and mayest no more open thy mouth because of thy confusion, when I shall be pacified toward thee for all that thou hast done, saith the Lord God.

la: aedifico quoque altare in domus Domini de qui dico Dominus in Hierusal sum nomen meus in aeternus
en: He built also altar in the house of the Lord, whereof the Lord had said: In Jerusalem shall my name be for ever.

la: et elefantis ostendo sanguis labrusca et morior ad acuo is in proelium
en: And they shewed the elephant the blood of grapes, and mulberries, to provoke them to fight.

la: et porta Vallis aedifico Anun et habitator Zanoe ipse aedifico is et statuo valva is et serus et vecto et mille cubo in murus usque ad porta Sterquilinii
en: And the gate of the valley Hanun built, and the inhabitant of Zanoe: they built it, and set up the door thereof, and the locks, and the bars, and a thousand cubit in the wall unto the gate of the dunghill.

la: facio igitur Levites et universus Judas iuxta omnis qui praecipio Ioiadae pontifex et ad-sumo singuli vir qui sub sui sum et venio per ordo sabbatum cum hic qui iam impleo sabbata et egredior sum siquidem Ioiadae pontifex non dimitto abeo turma qui sui per singulus ebdomadas succedo con-suesco
en: So the Levites, and all Juda did according to all that Joiada the high priest had commanded: and they took every one his men that were under him, and that came in by the course of the sabbath, with those who had fulfilled the sabbath, and were to go out. For Joiada the high priest permitted not the company to depart, which were accustomed to succeed one another every week.

la: quomodo enim possum sustineo nex et interfectio populus meus
en: For how can I endure the murdering and slaughter of my people?

la: si enim amissio is reconciliatio sum mundus qui assumptio nisi vito ex morior
en: For if the loss of them be the reconciliation of the world, what shall the receiving of them be, but life from the dead?

la: Tracta singulus in totus solus primus ponito, deinde de mortarium traho linito, traho addo singulatim, item linitus usque adeo, donec omnis caseus cum mel abutor eris.
en: Place a first layer of separate tracta over the whole crust, cover it with the mixture from the bowl, add the tracta one by one, covering each layer until you have used up all the cheese and honey.

la: et oleum unctio fundo super caput is atque hic ritus consecro
en: And thou shalt pour the oil of unction upon his head: and by this rite shall he be consecrated.

la: ut offertor holocaustum Domino super altare holocaustomatis jugis mane et vesperus iuxta omnis qui scribo sum in lex Domini quam praecipio Israhelis
en: That they should offer holocaust to the Lord upon the altar of holocaust continually, morning and evening, according to all that is written in the law of the Lord, which he commanded Israel.

la: sepelieruntque is in civitas David cum rex is qui facio bonus cum Israhel et cum domus is
en: And they buried him in the city of David among the kings, because he had done good to Israel, and to his house.

la: annus centesimus octogesimus octavus populus qui sum Hierosolyma et in Judaeus senatus et Judas Aristobolo magister Ptolomei rex qui sum de genus christor sacerdos et hic qui in Aegyptus sum Judaeus salus et sanitas
en: In the year one hundred and eighty-eight, the people that is at Jerusalem, and in Judea, and the senate, and Judas, to Aristobolus, the preceptor of king Ptolemee, who is of the stock of the anointed priests, and to the Jews that are in Egypt, health and welfare.

la: loquor sum Dominus ad Mosen
en: And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:

la: quia non introeo in cor is sed in venter et in secedo exeo purgo omnis esca
en: Because it entereth not into his heart but goeth into his belly and goeth out into the privy, purging all meats?

la: cunctaris in circuitus gens qui iuxta vel procul sum ab initium usque ad finis terra
en: Of all the nation round about, that are near or afar off, from one end of the earth to the other,

la: reliquus verus opus Salomon prior et novus scribo sum in verbum Nathan propheta et in liber Ahiae Silonitis in visio quoque Iaddo video contra Hieroboam filius Nabath
en: Now the rest of the act of Solomon first and last are written in the word of Nathan the prophet, and in the book of Ahias the Silonite, and in the vision of Addo the seer, against Jeroboam the son of Nabat.

la: adquiesco igitur is et habeo pax et per hic habeo fructus bonus
en: Submit thyself then to him, and be at peace: and thereby thou shalt have the best fruits.

la: in similitudo lapis aqua duro et superficies abyssus constringo
en: The water are hardened like a stone, and the surface of the deep is congealed.

la: cum adsum dies septimus dico ad uxor Samson blandio vir tuus et suadeo is ut indico tu quis significo problema qui si facio nolo incendo et tu et domus pater tuus an idcirco nos voco ad nuptiae ut spolio
en: And when the seventh day came, they said to the wife of Samson: Sooth thy husband, and persuade him to tell thee what the riddle meaneth. But if thou wilt not do it, we will burn thee, and thy father's house. Have you called u to the wedding on purpose to strip us?

la: qui egredior in-ruo super occido ceterus filius Jacob et depopulor sum urbs in ultio stuprum
en: And when they were gone out, the other son of Jacob came upon the slain; and plundered the city in revenge of the rape.

la: Si sex iugum vasum opus erit, facito.
en: If necessary, supply six complete equipments.

la: Ad hic populus Romanus iam ab principium imperium bonus video amicus quam servus quaerere, tueor reor volo quam cogo imperitare.
en: In addition to this, there is the fact that the Roman people from the beginning of their rule have preferred to seek friend rather than slaves; they have thought it safer to govern the willing than those forced to obey.

la: ex-surio impleo bonus et dives dimitto inanis
en: He hath filled the hungry with good things: and the rich he hath sent empty away.

la: et erubesco ex omnis qui facio figura domus et fabrica is exitus et introitus et omnis descriptio is et universus praecipio is cunctus ordo is et omnis lex is ostendo is et scribo in oculus is et custodio omnis descriptio is et praecipio ille et facio is
en: And be ashamed of all that they have done. Shew them the form of the house, and of the fashion thereof, the going out and the coming in, and the whole plan thereof, and all it ordinances, and all it order, and all it laws, and thou shalt write it in their sight: that they may keep the whole form thereof, and it ordinances, and do them.

la: sanctificatio is desolo sum sicut solitudo dies festus is converro sum in luctus sabbata is in opprobrium honor is in nihilis
en: Her sanctuary wa desolate like a wilderness, her festival day were turned into mourning, her sabbath into reproach, her honour were brought to nothing.

la: turpitudo et ignominia congrego sui et opprobrium ille non deleo
en: He gathereth to himself shame and dishonour, and his reproach shall not be blotted out:

la: qui tango cadaver homo et propter hic septem dies sum immundus
en: He that toucheth the corpse of a man, and is therefore unclean seven days,

la: tertius quoque sum bellum in Gob contra Philistheos in quo percutio Adeodatus filius Saltus polymitarius bethleemites Goliath Gettheum qui hastilis hasta sum quasi liciatorium texentium
en: And there wa a third battle in Gob against the Philistines, in which Adeodatus the son of the Forrest an embroiderer of Bethlehem slew Goliath the Gethite, the shaft of whose spear wa like a weaver's beam.

la: paruus sum cunctus miseratio et veritas quam ex-pleo servo tuus in baculus meus transeo Jordanes iste et nunc cum duo turma regredior
en: I am not worthy of the least of all thy mercies, and of thy truth which thou hast fulfilled to thy servant. With my staff I passed over this Jordan; and now I return with two companies.

la: Decessit annus ferme sextus et quinquagesimo: de quo si quis ambiget, recurro ad prior consulatus eius, in qui creo sum annus octavus et tricesimo: ita dubitaris desinet.
en: He died in his fifty-sixth year. If anyone question this let him call to mind his first consulship, to which he wa elected in his thirty-eighth year, and he will cease to doubt.

la: et respondeo ille Iesus dico quis volo tu facio caecus autem dico is rabboni ut video
en: And Jesus answering, said to him: What wilt thou that I should do to thee? And the blind man said to him: Rabboni. That I may see.

la: Vos pro libertate, quam ab ille accepistis, nonne summus ops nitemini'atque is vehementius, quo magnus dedecus sum pario amitto quam omnino non paro punc Dicet aliquis Quid igitur censes? Vindicandum in is qui hostis prodo res publicam, non manus neque vi, qui magis tu facio quam ille adcidisse indignus est, verus quaestio et indicium ipse Iugurthae.
en: will you not do everything in your power in defense of the liberty which they bequeathed to you'and all the more ardently, seeing that it is a greater disgrace to lose what ha been won than never to have acquired it? Someone will say, What then do you advise? My view is that those who have betrayed their country to the enemy must be punished, yet not by might and not by violence (which it is a le becoming act for you to perform than for them to suffer) but rather by the court and by Jugurthas own testimony.

la: et tamen frater ipse cognosco non sum agnitus ab is
en: And though he knew his brethren, he wa not known by them.

la: dico ubi sum cessaris facio ex homo memoria is
en: I said: Where are they? I will make the memory of them to cease from among men.

la: ubi non sum saepes diripio possessio et ubi non sum mulier gemescit egeo
en: Where there is no hedge, the possession shall be spoiled: and where there is no wife, he mourneth that is in want.

la: lavo in is Aaron et filius is manus suus atque pes
en: Aaron and his son shall wash their hand and foot in it:

la: audio verbum Domini princeps Sodoma percipio auris lex Dei noster populus Gomorra
en: Hear the word of the Lord, ye ruler of Sodom, give ear to the law of our God, ye people of Gomorrha.

la: Tum senatus populus Romanus L. Aemilius Paulum, qui et praetor et consul triumphaverat, vir in tantus laudandum, in quantus intellego virtus potest, consul creavit.
en: Then the senate and the Roman people chose a consul Lucius Aemilius Paulus, who had previously triumphed, both in his praetorship and in his consulship, a man worthy of the highest praise that can be associated with valour.

la: si quis adipem qui offertor debeo in incendo Domini comedo pereo de populus suus
en: If any man eat the fat that should be offered for the burnt sacrifice of the Lord, he shall perish out of his people.

la: do qui dormio cum is pater puella quinquaginta siclos argentum et habeo is uxor quia humilio ille non possum dimitto cunctus dies vita suus
en: He that lay with her shall give to the father of the maid fifty sicles of silver, and shall have her to wife, because he hath humbled her: he may not put her away all the day of his life.

la: Noga quoque et Napheg et Iaphiae
en: And Noga, and Napheg, and Japhia,

la: ergo puto sum qui verus Deus habito super terra si enim caelum et caelum caelum tu capio non possum quantus magis domus hic quam aedifico
en: Is it then to be thought that God should indeed dwell upon earth? for if heaven, and the heaven of heavens, cannot contain thee, how much le this house which I have built?

la: tres annus regno in Hierusal nomen mater is Maacha filia Absalom
en: He reigned three year in Jerusalem: the name of his mother wa Maacha, the daughter of Abessalom.

la: tunc demum reminisco pincernaris magister aio confiteor peccatum meus
en: Then at length the chief butler remembering, said: I confess my sin:

la: respondeo Tobias dico pater quam merces do is aut quis dignus possum sum beneficium is
en: Tobias answering, said to his father: Father, what wage shall we give him? or what can be worthy of his benefits?

la: ab magnitudo enim species et creatura cognoscibiliter possum hic creator video
en: For by the greatness of the beauty, and of the creature, the creator of them may be seen, so a to be known thereby.

la: loquor sum Dominus ad Mosen dico
en: And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:

la: Sequens fortuna suus Caesar perveho in Africa est, quam occido C. Curione, Iulianaris dux partium, Pompejanus obtineo exercitus.
en: Caesar, following up his success, passed over to Africa, of which the Pompeian army now held possession since the death of Gaius Curio, the leader there of the Caesarian party.

la: et tollo reliquiae fragmentor duodecim cofinos plenus et de piscis
en: And they took up the leavings, twelve full basket of fragments, and of the fishes.

la: et nos tu ad-nuntio is qui ad pater noster repromissio facio sum
en: And we declare unto you that the promise which wa made to our fathers,

la: et in unus omnis populus congrego tam vis quam mulier parvulis et advenio qui sum intra porta tuus ut audio disco et timeo Dominum Deum vester et custodio impleo omnis sermo lex hic
en: And the people being all assembled together, both men and women, child and strangers, that are within thy gates: that hearing they may learn, and fear the Lord your God, and keep, and fulfil all the word of this law:

la: cum voveo voveo Domino Deo tuus non tardo reddo quia requiro ille Dominus Deus tuus et si moror sum reputo tu in peccatum
en: When thou hast made a vow to the Lord thy God, thou shalt not delay to pay it: because the Lord thy God will require it. And if thou delay, it shall be imputed to thee for a sin.

la: Consulis animus tamen paulus adrectus.
en: Still, the consul spirit wa somewhat buoyed.

la: facio enim Dominus tu sicut loquor sum in manus meus et scindo regnum de manus tuus et do ille propior tuus David
en: For the Lord will do to thee a he spoke by me, and he will rend thy kingdom out of thy hand, and will give it to thy neighbour David:

la: si enim facio facio verbum iste ingredior per porta domus hic rex sedeo de genus David super thronus is et ascendo currus et equus ipse et servio et populus is
en: For if you will do this thing indeed, then shall there enter in by the gate of this house, king of the race of David sitting upon his throne, and riding in chariot and on horses, they and their servants, and their people.

la: caro fors co-medeor et sanguis princeps terra bibo aries agnus et hircorum taurus altilis et pinguis omnis
en: You shall eat the flesh of the mighty, and you shall drink the blood of the prince of the earth, of rams, and of lambs, and of he goats, and bullocks, and of all that are well fed and fat.

la: dico ad Nathan propheta video qui ego habito in domus cedrinus et arca Dei pono sum in medium pellis
en: He said to Nathan the prophet: Dost thou see that I dwell in a house of cedar, and the ark of God is lodged within skins?

la: dico ego portendo vester quomodo facio sic fio ille in transmigratio et captivitas eo
en: Say: I am a sign of thing to come to you: a I have done, so shall it be done to them: they shall be removed from their dwellings, and go into captivity.

la: et pono spatium iter inter sui et gener dies tres qui pasco reliquus grex is
en: And he set the space of three days' journey betwixt himself and his son in law, who fed the rest of his flock.

la: hic filius Rahel qui gigno Jacob omnis anima quattuordecim
en: These are the son of Rachel, whom she bore to Jacob: all the souls, fourteen.

la: video itaque filius Israhel fugio ille descendo clango tuba et ululo post ipse
en: So the child of Israel seeing them fleeing, followed after them. And they went down sounding with trumpet and shouting after them.

la: qui facio iuxta verbum ille et aufero musca ab Pharao et ab servio et ab populus is non supersum ne unus quidem
en: And he did according to his word: and he took away the fly from Pharao, and from his servants, and from his people: there wa not left so much a one.

la: et ut ad-propio Azotus ostendo is templum Dagon succendo et Azotus et ceterus is demolio et corpus projectum et is qui caedo sum in bellum tumulus qui facio secus via
en: And when he came near to Azotus, they shewed him the temple of Dagon that wa burnt with fire, and Azotus, and the suburb thereof, that were destroyed, and the body that were cast abroad, and the graf of them that were slain in the battle, which they had made near the way.

la: et aspicio inimicus meus et operio confusio qui dico ad ego ubi sum Dominus Deus tuus oculus meus video in is nunc sum in conculcatio ut lutum platearis
en: And my enemy shall behold, and she shall be covered with shame, who saith to me: Where is the Lord thy God? my eye shall look down upon her: now shall she be trodden under foot a the mire of the streets.

la: nam cum fio vox supra firmamentum qui sum super caput is sto et summitto ala suus
en: For when a voice came from above the firmament, that wa over their heads, they stood, and let down their wings.

la: Zabulon verus et Nepthalim offertor anima suus mors in regio Merome
en: But Zabulon and Nephthali offered their life to death in the region of Merome.

la: ineo consilium et dissipabitur loquor verbum et non fio quia nos Deus
en: Take counsel together, and it shall be defeated: speak a word, and it shall not be done: because God is with us.

la: ex quo frater tuus Judas defungor sum vir similis is non sum qui exeo contra inimicus Bacchis et is qui inimicus sum gens noster
en: Since thy brother Judas died there is not a man like him to go forth against our enemies, Bacchides, and them that are the enemy of our nation.

la: renovo autem spiritus mens vester
en: And be renewed in spirit of your mind:

la: et congrego nongenti falcatus currus omnis exercitus de Aroseth gens ad torreo Cison
en: And he gathered together his nine hundred chariot armed with scythes, and all his army, from Haroseth of the Gentiles, to the torrent Cison.

la: sumo tu dies primus fructus arbor pulcher spatula palmaris et ramus lignum densaris frondium et salix de torreo et laeto coram Domino Deo vester
en: And you shall take to you on the first day the fruit of the fairest tree, and branch of palm trees, and bough of thick trees, and willow of the brook: And you shall rejoice before the Lord your God.

la: ideo notus tu facio qui nemo in Spiritu Dei loquor dico anathema Iesus et nemo possum dico Dominus Iesus nisi in Spiritu Sancto
en: Wherefore, I give you to understand that no man, speaking by the Spirit of God, saith Anathema to Jesus. And no man can say The Lord Jesus, but by the Holy Ghost.

la: homo quicumque facio similis ut odor ille perfruor pereo de populus suus
en: What man soever shall make the like, to enjoy the smell thereof, he shall perish out of his people.

la: de animabus homo sedecim mille cedo in pars Domini triginta duo anima
en: Out of the sixteen thousand persons, there fell to the portion of the Lord, thirty-two souls.

la: non sum deficio neque laboro in is non dormito neque dormio neque solvo cingulis renum is neque rumpo corrigia calceamentum is
en: There is none that shall faint, nor labour among them: they shall not slumber nor sleep, neither shall the girdle of their loin be loosed, nor the latchet of their shoe be broken.

la: et aio dito ego Deus dos bonus etiam hic vicus ego sum maritus meus is qui gigno is sex filius et idcirco appello nomen is Zabulon
en: And said: God hath endowed me with a good dowry: this turn also my husband will be with me, because I have borne him six sons: and therefore she called his name Zabulon.

la: et hic sum annuntiatio quam audio ab is et ad-nuntio tu quoniam Deus lux sum et tenebra in is non sum ullus
en: And this is the declaration which we have heard from him and declare unto you: That God is light and in him there is no darkness.

la: qui gigno Laadan hic quoque filius Ammiud gigno Elisama
en: Who begot Laadan: and his son wa Ammiud, who begot Elisama,

la: et quondam vincio pariter sine molestia non audio voco exactor
en: And they sometime bound together without disquiet, have not heard the voice of the oppressor.

la: ut non segnis efficio verus imitator is qui fides et patientia heredito promissio
en: That you become not slothful, but follower of them who through faith and patience shall inherit the promises.

la: et clamo leo super speculum Domini ego sum sto jugis per dies et super custodia meus ego sum sto totus nox
en: And a lion cried out: I am upon the watchtower of the Lord, standing continually by day: and I am upon my ward, standing whole nights.

la: nos autem circumdo multus tribulatio et multus proelio et in-pugno nos rex qui sum in circuitus noster
en: But we have had many trouble and war on every side; and the king that are round about u have fought against us.

la: vito enim sum invenio is et universus caro sanitas
en: For they are life to those that find them, and health to all flesh.

la: et ecce dies tertius quando gravis vulnus dolor sum arrepo duo Jacob filius Symeon et Levi frater Dinae gladius ingredior sum urbs confidenter interfacio omnis masculis
en: And behold the third day, when the pain of the wound wa greatest, two of the son of Jacob, Simeon and Levi, the brother of Dina, taking their swords, entered boldly into the city, and slew all the men:

la: filius Ceros filius Siaa filius Phadon
en: The child of Ceros, the child of Sia, the child of Phadon,

la: et sum fortitudo is in direptio et domus is in desertum et aedifico domus et non habito et planto vinea et non bibo vinum is
en: And their strength shall become a booty, and their house a a desert: and they shall build houses, and shall not dwell in them: and they shall plant vineyards, and shall not drink the wine of them.

la: quam ob res in ipse foris accedo ad dispensator
en: Wherefore, going up to the steward of the house, at the door,

la: sin autem audio voco Domini Dei tuus ut facio atque custodio omnis mandatum is qui ego praecipio tu hodie facio tu Dominus Deus tuus excello cunctus gens qui verso in terra
en: Now if thou wilt hear the voice of all his commandments, which I command thee this day, the Lord thy God will make thee higher than all the nation that are on the earth.

la: Vicini quo pacisco niteant, is animus advertito: in bonus regio bene niteo oportebit.
en: Notice how the neighbour keep up their places; if the district is good, they should be well kept.

la: Genus homo salubris corpore, velox, patior laborum.
en: The race of men here are physically fit, fleet of foot, and capable of strenuous exertion.

la: si fors audio domus Judas universus malus qui ego cogo facio is revorto unusquisque ab via suus malus et propitius sum iniquitas et pecco is
en: If so be, when the house of Juda shall hear all the evil that I purpose to do unto them, that they may return every man from his wicked way: and I will forgive their iniquity, and their sin.

la: dico praecipio praecipio tu ne doceo in nomen iste et ecce re-pleo Hierusal doctrina vester et volo induco super nos sanguis homo iste
en: Saying: Commanding, we commanded you that you should not teach in this name. And behold, you have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine: and you have a mind to bring the blood of this man upon us.

la: sin autem declino ab vir tuus atque polluo sum et concubo cum alter
en: But if thou hast gone aside from thy husband, and art defiled, and hast lain with another man:

la: si paupertas con-pello vendo sui tu frater tuus non is opprimo servitus famulus
en: If thy brother constrained by poverty, sell himself to thee: thou shalt not oppress him with the service of bondservants.

la: qui sequor rex Israhel qui persequor canis mortuus sequor et pulex unus
en: After whom dost thou pursue? After a dead dog, after a flea.

la: ecce tu omnis nosco et quis sine causa vanus loquor
en: Behold you all know it, and why do you speak vain thing without cause?

la: et prope sum pascha Judaeus et ascendo Hierosolyma Iesus
en: And the pasch of the Jews wa at hand: and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.

la: ecce quasi leo ascendo de superbia Jordanes ad pulchritudo robustus quia subeo curro is facio ad ille et quis sum eligo qui praepono is quis enim similis meus et quis sustineo ego et quis sum iste pastor qui resisto vultus meus
en: Behold one shall come up a a lion from the swelling of the Jordan, against the strong and beautiful: for I will make him run suddenly upon her: and who shall be the chosen one whom I may appoint over her? for who is like to me? and who shall abide me? and who is that shepherd that can withstand my countenance?

la: neque intendo fabula et genealogia intermino qui quaestio praesto magis quam aedificatio Dei qui sum in fides
en: Not to give heed to fable and endless genealogies, which furnish question rather than the edification of God which is in faith

la: Ita qui sum in Caesaris potestate, qui et totus sunt, quomodo habeo salus Caesaris in potestate, ut is praesto possum videantur, quam facilis ipse ab Caesaris consequantur? Ideo ergo committo in maiestas imperatoris, quia ille non subicio res suis, qui ab non ludo de officium salus ipse qui is non puto in manus sum plumbatis.
en: So, I ask, how will they, who are in Caesars power, who belong to Caesar outright, have Caesars safety in their power, that you should suppose them able to secure for him the safety which they themselves more easily have from Caesar? So, after all, our crime against the majesty of the Emperors come to this: that we do not subordinate them to their property; that we do not make a jest of our care for their safety, and do not think it really lie in hand soldered on with lead.b

la: et populus paupero salvus facies oculus tuus excello humilio
en: And the poor people thou wilt save: and with thy eye thou shalt humble the haughty.

la: et video Tryfon quia venio cum exercitus multus ut extendo in is manus et timeo
en: Now when Tryphon saw that Jonathan came with a great army, he durst not stretch forth his hand against him.

la: de tribus Ruben Semmua filius Zecchur
en: Of the tribe of Ruben, Sammua the son of Zechur.

la: et effundo ille super omnis opus suus et super omnis caro secundus do suus et praebeo ille diligo sui
en: And he poured her out upon all his works, and upon all flesh according to his gift, and hath given her to them that love him.

la: dico ad is rex quis volo Hester regina qui sum petitio tuus etiam si dimidia regnum pars peto do tu
en: And the king said to her: What wilt thou, queen Esther? what is thy request? if thou shouldst even ask one half of the kingdom, it shall be given to thee.

la: et nuntio sum David qui facio Respha filia Ahia concubina Saul
en: And it wa told David, what Respha the daughter of Aia, the concubine of Saul, had done.

la: idem hora sermo conpletus sum super Nabuchodonosor ex homo abicio sum et faenum ut bos comedo et ros caelum corpus is inficio sum donec capillus is in similitudo aquilaris cresco et unguis is quasi avis
en: The same hour the word wa fulfilled upon Nabuchodonosor, and he wa driven away from among men, and did eat grass, like an ox, and his body wa wet with the dew of heaven: till his hair grew like the feather of eagles, and his nail like birds' claws.

la: probo autem sui ipse homo et sic de panis ille edo et de calix bibo
en: But let a man prove himself: and so let him eat of that bread and drink of the chalice.

la: qui dico Deo recedo ab nos et quasi nihil possum facio Omnipotens aestimo is
en: Who said to God: Depart from us: and looked upon the Almighty a if he could do nothing:

la: numquid alligo rinocerota ad aro lorus tuus aut confringo glaeba valles post tu
en: Canst thou bind the rhinoceros with thy thong to plough, or will he break the clod of the valley after thee?

la: loquor sum Dominus ad Mosen dico
en: And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:

la: et dissipabuntur in medium terra desolataris et urbs is in medium civitas desertaris sum
en: And they shall be desolate in the midst of the land that are desolate, and the city thereof shall be in the midst of the city that are wasted.

la: et ecce gaudium et laetitia occaedes vitulus et iugulo aries co-medeor caro et bibo vinum comedamus et bibo creo enim morior
en: And behold joy and gladness, killing calves, and slaying rams, eating flesh, and drinking wine: Let u eat and drink; for to morrow we shall die.

la: ego confido in tu in Domino qui nihil alius sapio qui autem conturbo tu porto iudicium quicumque sum ille
en: I have confidence in you in the Lord that you will not be of another mind: but he that troubleth you shall bear the judgment, whosoever he be.

la: quicumque possum manus tuus facio instanter operaris quia neque opus neque ratio neque scientia neque sapientia sum apud inferi quo tu propero
en: Whatsoever thy hand is able to do, do it earnestly: for neither work, nor reason, nor wisdom, nor knowledge shall be in hell, whither thou art hastening.

la: si autem oberro derelinquo is et trado ille in manus inimicus suus
en: But if he go astray, she will forsake him, and deliver him into the hand of his enemy.

la: rex autem Syria praecipio dux equito suus dico ne pugno contra paruus aut contra magnus nisi contra solus rex Israhel
en: Now the king of Syria had commanded the captain of his cavalry, saying: Fight ye not with small, or great, but with the king of Israel only.

la: porro Mesellamiae filius et frater robustus decem et octo
en: And the son of Meselemia, and their brother strong men, were eighteen.

la: hic unus consilium habeo et virtus et potestas suus bestia trado
en: These have one design: and their strength and power they shall deliver to the beast.

la: et stupeo ad terror is qui video oculus tuus
en: And be astonished at the terror of those thing which thy eye shall see:

la: dico autem is servio suus quis sum sermo qui facio propter infer cum adhuc vivo jejuno et fleo mortuus autem puer surgo et comedisti panis
en: And his servant said to him: What thing is this that thou hast done? thou didst fast and weep for the child, while it wa alive, but when the child wa dead, thou didst rise up, and eat bread.

la: et exeo fama hic in universus terra ille
en: And the fame hereof went abroad into all that country.

la: CXXXVIII. Boves feriae coniungo licet. Haec licet facere: arvehant ligna, fabalia, frumentum, qui condio erit.
en: CXXXVIII. Oxen may be yoked on feast day for these purposes: to haul firewood, bean stalks, and grain for storing.

la: Ruben Symeon Levi Judas
en: Ruben, Simeon, Levi, Juda,

la: Ceterum quo multus bene atque strenuus fecisset, is animus suus iniuria paruus tolerare.
en: But, he said, the more numerous his act of virtue and courage had been, the le his spirit wa tolerant of injury.

la: et sedeo Iesus contra gazofilacium aspicio quomodo turba iacto aes in gazofilacium et multus dives jacto multus
en: And Jesus sitting over against the treasury, beheld how the people cast money into the treasury. And many that were rich cast in much.

la: qui aufero stillo pluvia et effundo imber ad instar gurges
en: He lifteth up the drop of rain, and poureth out shower like floods:

la: sum itaque numerus is qui manus ad os proicio aqua lambuerant trecenti vir omnis autem reliquus multitudo flecto poples bibo
en: And the number of them that had lapped water; casting it with the hand to their mouth, wa three hundred men: and all the rest of the multitude had drunk kneeling.

la: et aio rex ubi sum filius dominus tuus respondeo Siba rex remaneo in Hierusal dico hodie restituo ego domus Israhel regnum pater meus
en: And the king said: Where is thy master's son? And Siba answered the king: He remained in Jerusalem, saying: To day, will the house of Israel restore me the kingdom of my father.

la: verumtamen quia non sum in manus is bonus suus consilium impii longus sum ab ego
en: Yet because their good thing are not in their hand, may the counsel of the wicked be far from me.

la: aut quis do homo commutatio pro anima suus
en: Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul:

la: quam vilis sum facio nimis itero via tuus et ab Aegyptus confundo sicut confundo sum ab Assur
en: How exceeding base art thou become, going the same way over again! and thou shalt be ashamed of Egypt, a thou wast ashamed of Assyria.

la: in consilium is ne venio anima meus et in coitus ille non sum gloria meus quia in furor suus occido vir et in voluntas suus suffodio murus
en: Let not my soul go into their counsel, nor my glory be in their assembly: because in their fury they slew a man, and in their selfwill they undermined a wall.

la: in hic omnis qui credo justifico
en: In him every one that believeth is justified.

la: et educo is de populus et congrego is de terra et induco is in terra suus et pasco is in mons Israhel in rivus et in cunctus sedes terra
en: And I will bring them out from the peoples, and will gather them out of the countries, and will bring them to their own land: and I will feed them in the mountain of Israel, by the rivers, and in all the habitation of the land.

la: dico autem is Iesus ego sum panis vita qui venio ad ego non ex-surio et qui credo in ego non sitio umquam
en: And Jesus said to them: I am the bread of life. He that cometh to me shall not hunger: and he that believeth in me shall never thirst.

la: quin et ego plaudo manus ad manus et impleo indignatio meus ego Dominus loquor sum
en: And I will clap my hand together, and will satisfy my indignation: I the Lord have spoken.

la: non sum tu pars neque sors in sermo iste cor enim tuus non sum recingo coram Deo
en: Thou hast no part nor lot in this matter. For thy heart is not right in the sight of God.

la: Ios verus et omnis Israhel cedo locus simulo metus et fugio per via solitudo
en: But Josue, and all Israel gave back, making a if they were afraid, and fleeing by the way of the wilderness.

la: omnis autem turba adoro cantor et hic qui teneo tuba sum in officium suus donec con-pleo holocaustum
en: And all the multitude adored, and the singers, and the trumpeters, were in their office till the holocaust wa finished.

la: et revorto omnis terra usque ad desertum de collis Remmon ad auster Hierusal et exalto et habito in locus suus ab porto Beniamin usque ad locus porta Prioris usque ad porta Angulorum et ab turris Ananehel usque ad torcularius rex
en: And all the land shall return even to the desert, from the hill to Remmon to the south of Jerusalem: and she shall be exalted, and shall dwell in her own place, from the gate of Benjamin even to the place of the former gate, and even to the gate of the corners: and from the tower of Hananeel even to the king's winepresses.

la: siquidem Dominus sonitus audio facio in castrum Syria currus et equus et exercitus plurimus dico ad invicem ecce merces conduco adverro nos rex Israhel rex Hettheorum et Aegyptius et venio super nos
en: For the Lord had made them hear, in the camp of Syria, the noise of chariots, and of horses, and of a very great army: and they said one to another: Behold, the king of Israel hath hired against u the king of the Hethites, and of the Egyptians; and they are come upon us.

la: mitto autem Dominus Deus pater suus ad ille per manus nuntius suus de nox consurgo et cottidie commoneo is qui parco populus et habitaculum suus
en: And the Lord the God of their father sent to them, by the hand of his messengers, rising early, and daily admonishing them: because he spared his people and his dwelling place.

la: et continuo curro unus ex is accipio spongia impleo acetum et inpono harundo et do is bibo
en: And immediately one of them running took a sponge and filled it with vinegar and put it on a reed and gave him to drink.

la: sin autem viduo vel repudio et absque liber revorto sum ad domus pater suus sicut puella consuo alo cibus pater suus omnis alienigenus co-medeor ex is non habeo potestas
en: But if she be a widow, or divorced, and having no child return to her father's house, she shall eat of her father's meats, a she wa wont to do when she wa a maid. No stranger hath leave to eat of them.

la: tunc Achior dux omnis filius Ammon respondeo aio si digno audio dominus meus dico veritas in conspectus tuus de populus iste qui in montanus habito et non egredior verbum falsus ex os meus
en: Then Achior captain of all the child of Ammon answering, said; If thou vouchsafe, my lord, to hear, I will tell the truth in thy sight concerning this people, that dwelleth in the mountains, and there shall not a false word come out of my mouth.

la: post is aedifico Levites Reum filius Benni post is aedifico Asebias princeps dimidia pars vinco Ceilae in vicus suus
en: After him built the Levites, Rehum the son of Benni. After him built Hasebias, lord of half the street of Ceila in his own street.

la: numquid grandis sum ut consolo tu Deus sed verbum tuus pravus hic prohibeo
en: Is it a great matter that God should comfort thee? but thy wicked word hinder this.

la: et hic tu sum nuntio audio in-quaero diligenter et verus sum reperio et abominatio facio sum in Israhel
en: And this is told thee, and hearing it thou hast inquired diligently, and found it to be true, and that the abomination is committed in Israel:

la: et omnis vir domus ille tam vernaculis quam empticius et alienigenus pariter circumcido sum
en: And all the men of his house, a well they that were born in his house, a the bought servant and stranger were circumcised with him.

la: et nunc congrego universi qui in civitas sum ut sponte nos trado omnis populus Holofernis
en: And now assemble ye all that are in the city, that we may of our own accord yield ourselves all up to the people of Holofernes.

la: divisio sacerdotalis et leviticaris in omnis opus domus Domini et in universus vasum ministerium templum Domini
en: And of the division of the priest and of the Levites, for all the work of the house of the Lord, and for all the vessel of the service of the temple of the Lord.

la: sed caput Syria Damascus et caput Damascus Rasin et adhuc sexa_ginta et quinque annus et desino Ephraim sum populus
en: But the head of Syria is Damascus, and the head of Damascus is Rasin: and within threescore and five years, Ephraim shall cease to be a people:

la: prophetes autem quidam senex habito in Bethel ad qui venio filius suus et narro is omnis opus qui facio vir Dei ille dies in Bethel et verbum qui loquor sum ad rex et narro pater suus
en: Now a certain old prophet dwelt in Bethel, and his son came to him, and told him all the work that the man of God had done that day in Bethel: and they told their father the word which he had spoken to the king.

la: et sum sicut avus fugio et pullus de nidus avolo sic sum filia Moab in transcendo Arnus
en: And it shall come to pass, that a a bird fleeing away, and a young one flying out of the nest, so shall the daughter of Moab be in the passage of Arnon.

la: Operculis inponito, relinquo qui interspiret.
en: Cover the jar, leaving space for air,

la: si statim ab annus incipio iobelei voveo ager quantus valeo possum tantus aestimo
en: If he vow his field immediately from the year of jubilee that is beginning: a much a it may be worth, at so much it shall be rated.

la: venio ergo Ahab in domus suus indignor et frendo super verbum qui loquor sum ad is Naboth Hiezrahelites dico non do tu hereditas pater meus et proicio sui in lectulis suus averto facies ad paries et non comedo panis
en: And Achab came into his house angry and fretting, because of the word that Naboth, the Jezrahelite, had spoken to him, saying: I will not give thee the inheritance of my fathers. And casting himself upon his bed, he turned away his face to the wall, and would eat no bread.

la: pravus sum cor omnis et inscrutabilis quis cognosco ille
en: The heart is perverse above all things, and unsearchable, who can know it?

la: et Asrihel ab quo familia Asrihelitaris et Sechem ab quo familia Sechemitaris
en: And Asriel, of whom is the family of the Asrielites: and Sechem, of whom is the family of the Sechemites:

la: igitur sors filius Judas per cognatio suus iste sum ab termino Edom desertum Sin contra meridio et usque ad extremus pars austral plaga
en: Now the lot of the child of Juda by their kindred wa this: From the frontier of Edom, to the desert of Sin southward, and to the uttermost part of the south coast.

la: sapientia foris praedico in platea do voco suus
en: Wisdom preacheth abroad, she uttereth her voice in the streets:

la: in verbum Sancti sto ad iudicium et non exardescent in vigilia suus
en: By the word of the holy one they stand in judgment, and shall never fall in their watches.

la: quamquam ego habeo confidentiam et in carnis si quis alius video confido in carnis ego magis
en: Though I might also have confidence in the flesh. If any other thinketh he may have confidence in the flesh, I more:

la: filius Meraris Mooli et Musium
en: The son of Merari, Moholi and Musi.

la: filius autem adulter inconsummatus sum et ab iniquus torus semen extermino
en: But the child of adulterer shall not come to perfection, and the seed of the unlawful bed shall be rooted out.

la: et declino populus in dies ille ingredior civitas quomodo declinaris soleo populus verro et fugio de proelium
en: And the people shunned the going into the city that day a a people would do that hath turned their backs, and fled away from the battle.

la: sed percutio Moabites in tempus ille circiter decem mille omnis robustus et fortis vir nullus is evado possum
en: But they slew of the Moabites at that time, about ten thousand, all strong and valiant men: none of them could escape.

la: et sicut parturio cor tuus fantasiam patior nisi ab Altissimo sum emitto visitatio ne do in ille cor tuus
en: And the heart fancieth a that of a woman in travail: except it be a vision sent forth from the most High, set not thy heart upon them.

la: nunc de propinquo effundo ira meus super tu et con-pleo furor meus in tu et iudico tu iuxta via tuus et in-pono tu omnis scelus tuus
en: Now very shortly I will pour out my wrath upon thee, and I will accomplish my anger in thee: and I will judge thee according to thy ways, and I will lay upon thee all thy crimes.

la: et ad-prehendo parens filia suus osculor sum is et dimitto eo
en: And the parent taking their daughter kissed her, and let her go:

la: ecce in iustitia regno rex et princeps in iudicium praesum
en: Behold a king shall reign in justice, and prince shall rule in judgment.

la: voco Jacob nomen locus ille Phanuhel dico video Deum facies ad facies et salvo facio sum anima meus
en: And Jacob called the name of the place Phanuel, saying: I have seen God face to face, and my soul ha been saved.

la: iterum dico ne quis ego puto insipiens alioqui velut insipiens accipio ego ut et ego modicus quis glorior
en: I say again (Let no man think me to be foolish: otherwise take me a one foolish, that I also may glory a little):

la: Metellus postquam video frustra inceptum, neque oppidum capio neque Jugurtha nisi ex insidiae aut suus locus pugna facio et iam aestas exigo esse, ab Zama discedo et in is urbs qui ad sui deficio sero munio locus aut moenia sum praesidium inponit.
en: After Metellus saw that his attempt wa in vain (that the town wa not being taken and that Jugurtha wa not offering to fight except from ambush or in a place advantageous to him) and that the summer wa now at an end, he left Zama and placed garrison in the city that had gone over to him and were strongly enough fortified by their position or by walls.

la: et habeo qui consolo anima tuus et enutrio senectus de nuru enim tuus nascor sum qui tu diligo et multus tu sum bonus quam si septem habeo filius
en: And thou shouldst have one to comfort thy soul, and cherish thy old age. For he is born of thy daughter in law: who loveth thee: and is much better to thee, than if thou hadst seven sons.

la: Occidit ergo ille rex, et trado Bel in potestas Danielis: qui subverto eum, et templum eius.
en: The king, therefore, put them ot death, and delivered Bel into the power of Daniel: who destroyed him and his temple.

la: aio iste sum sermo qui iubeo Dominus fio
en: He said: This is the word that the Lord hath commanded to be done.

la: extremus quoque frater suus quinque vir statuo coram rex
en: Five men also, the last of his brethren, he presented before the king:

la: et salvo tu ex universus inquinamentum vester et voco frumentum et multiplico ille et non in-pono in tu fames
en: And I will save you from all your uncleannesses: and I will call for corn, and will multiply it, and will lay no famine upon you.

la: nolo fio pro amicus inimicus propior improperium enim et contumelia malus heredito et omnis peccator invidus et bilinguis
en: Instead of a friend become not an enemy to thy neighbour: for an evil man shall inherit reproach and shame, so shall every sinner that is envious and double tongued.

la: dico autem Paulus ad tribunal Caesaris sto ubi ego oportet iudico Judaeus non noceo sicut tu bonus nosco
en: Then Paul said: I stand at Caesar's judgment seat, where I ought to be judged. To the Jews I have done no injury, a thou very well knowest.

la: fugio Zebee et Salmana qui persequor Gedeon comprehendo turbo omnis exercitus is
en: And Zebee and Salmana fled, and Gedeon pursued and took them, all their host being put in confusion.

la: quoniam rapio sum in paradisus et audio arcanus verbum qui non licet homo loquor
en: That he wa caught up into paradise and heard secret word which it is not granted to man to utter.

la: Abraham autem consurgo mane ubi sto prior cum Domino
en: And Abraham got up early in the morning, and in the place where he had stood before with the Lord:

la: Et hic amplus lotium conservo is qui brassica essitarit, is calfacito, is homo demittito, cito sanus facies hic cura; experior hic est.
en: And still further, if you save the urine of a person who eats cabbage habitually, heat it, and bathe the patient in it, he will be healed quickly; this remedy ha been tested.

la: et dico sic sub-mergo Babylon et non consurgo ab facies adflictio quam ego adduco super is et dissolvo hucusque verbum Hieremias
en: And thou shalt say: Thus shall Babylon sink, and she shall not rise up from the affliction that I will bring upon her, and she shall be utterly destroyed. Thus far are the word of Jeremias.

la: et invoco Dominum Deum et aio Domine non sum apud tu ullus disto utrum in paucus auxilio an in multus adjuvo nos Domine Deus noster in tu enim et in tuus nomen habeo fiducia venio contra hic multitudo Domine Deus noster tu sum non praevaleo contra tu homo
en: And he called upon the Lord God, and said: Lord, there is no difference with thee, whether thou help with few, or with many: help us, O Lord our God: for with confidence in thee, and in thy name we are come against this multitude. O Lord thou art our God, let not man prevail against thee.

la: quare discipulis tuus transgredior traditio senex non enim lavo manus suus cum panis manduco
en: Why do thy disciple transgress the tradition of the ancients? For they wash not their hand when they eat bread.

la: domus autem suus aedifico Salomon tredecim annus et ad perficio usque perduco
en: And Solomon built his own house in thirteen years, and brought it to perfection.

la: tunc Nabuchodonosor rex obstipesco et surgo properus et aio optimas suus nonne tres vir mitto in medium ignis conpeditos qui respondeo dico rex verus rex
en: Then Nabuchodonosor, the king, wa astonished, and rose up in haste, and said to his nobles: Did we not cast three men bound into the midst of the fire? They answered the king, and said: True, O king.

la: et ut libero ab importunus et malus homo non enim omnis sum fides
en: And that we may be delivered from importunate and evil men: for all men have not faith.

la: ut probo potis ut sum sincero et sine offendo in dies Christus
en: That you may approve the better things: that you may be sincere and without offence unto the day of Christ:

la: diaconus similis pudicus non bilinguis non multus vinum dedo non turpis lucrum sector
en: Deacons in like manner: chaste, not double tongued, not given to much wine, not greedy of filthy lucre:

la: filius Iafeth Gomer Magog Madai et Iavan Thubal Mosoch Thiras
en: The son of Japheth: Gomer, and Magog, and Madai, and Javan, Thubal, Mosoch, Thiras.

la: respondeo Mifiboseth rex etiam cunctus accipio postquam revorto sum dominus meus rex pacificus in domus suus
en: And Miphiboseth answered the king: Yea, let him take all, forasmuch a my lord the king is returned peaceably into his house.

la: et venio ab orior et occaedes et aquilo et auster et accumbo in regnum Dei
en: And there shall come from the east and the west and the north and the south: and shall sit down in the kingdom of God.

la: fides et ipse Sarra sterilis virtus in conceptio semen accipio etiam praeter tempus aetas quoniam fidelis credo sum qui promitto
en: By faith also Sara herself, being barren, received strength to conceive seed, even past the time of age: because she believed that he wa faithful who had promised,

la: in resurrectio enim neque nubo neque nubo sed sum sicut angelus Dei in caelum
en: For in the resurrection they shall neither marry nor be married, but shall be a the angel of God in heaven.

la: surgo ergo et fugio in tenebrae et derelinquo tentorius suus et equus et asinus in castrum fugio anima tantus suus salvaris cupio
en: Wherefore they arose, and fled away in the dark, and left their tents, and their horse and ass in the camp, and fled, desiring to save their lives.

la: quam asper sum nimium sapientia indoctus homo et non permaneo in ille excors
en: How very unpleasant is wisdom to the unlearned, and the unwise will not continue with her.

la: exerceo etiam potestas super cunctus rex ab fluvius Eufraten usque ad terra Philisthinorum is sum usque ad terminus Aegyptius
en: And he exercised authority over all the king from the river Euphrates to the land of the Philistines, and to the border of Egypt.

la: et qui servo mandatum is in ille maneo et ipse in is et in hic scio quoniam maneo in nos de Spiritu qui nos do
en: And he that keepeth his commandment abideth in him, and he in him. And in this we know that he abideth in u by the Spirit which he hath given us.

la: qui autem reliquus sum aufero ex is morior et non in sapientia
en: And they that shall be left, shall be taken away from them: they shall die, and not in wisdom.

la: et do sum is os loquor magnus et blasphemia et do sum ille potestas facio mensis quadraginta duo
en: And there wa given to him a mouth speaking great thing and blasphemies: and power wa given to him to do, two and forty months.

la: et venio David ad Saul et sto coram is at ille diligo is nimis et facio sum is armiger
en: And David came to Saul, and stood before him: and he loved him exceedingly, and made him his armourbearer.

la: et facio in furor et in indignatio ultio in omnis gens qui non audio
en: And I will execute vengeance in wrath, and in indignation, among all the nation that have not given ear.

la: HE facio sum in derideo omnis populus meus canticum is totus dies
en: He. I am made a derision to all my people, their song all the day long.

la: et elevo ego spiritus et introduco ego ad porta domus Domini oriental qui respicio sol orior et ecce in introeo porta viginti quinque vir et video in medium is Hiezoniam filius Azur et Pheltiam filius Banaiae princeps populus
en: And the spirit lifted me up, and brought me into the east gate of the house of the Lord, which looketh towards the rising of the sun: and behold in the entry of the gate five and twenty men: and I saw in the midst of them Jezonias the son of Azur, and Pheltias the son of Banaias, prince of the people.

la: memento ut dies sabbatum sanctifico
en: Remember that thou keep holy the sabbath day.

la: et mel et butyrum ovo et pinguis vitulus do David et populus qui cum is sum ad vesco suspicor enim sum populus fames et sitis fatigo in desero
en: And honey, and butter, and sheep, and fat calves, and they gave to David and the people that were with him, to eat: for they suspected that the people were faint with hunger and thirst in the wilderness.

la: nolo avidus sum in omnis epulatio et non tu effundo super omnis esca
en: Be not greedy in any feasting, and pour not out thyself upon any meat:

la: qui respondeo is eo cum pax Dominus respicio via vester et iter quo pergo
en: He answered them: Go in peace: the Lord looketh on your way, and the journey that you go.

la: Deinde neque dum Hannibal in Italia moratur, neque propior post excedo is annus vaco Romanus colonia condere, cum sum in bellum conquaero potis miles quam dimitto et post bellum vireo refovendae magis quam spargendae.
en: Thereafter, during Hannibals stay in Italy, and in the next few year subsequent to his departure, the Romans had no leisure for the founding of colonies, since, while the war lasted, they had to find soldiers, rather than muster them out, and, after it wa over, the strength of the city needed to be revived and concentrated rather than to be dispersed.

la: Nam ille quidem pigeo dicere, hic annus quindecim quam ludibrium sum superbia paucorum, quam foedus quisque inultus pereo vester defensores, ut tu animus ab ignavia atque socordia corrumpo sit, qui ne nunc quidem, obnoxius inimicis, exsurgitis atque etiam nunc timeo is qui decet terror esse.
en: For it grief me to state certain facts: how during the past fifteen year you have been the plaything of a few men insolence; how shamefully and without being avenged your defender have perished; how your spirit ha been corrupted a a consequence of cowardice and indolence; even now you take no action, when your enemy are at your mercy, and even now you fear those in whom you should be inspiring fear.

la: homo qui trado anima suus pro nomen Domini noster Iesus Christus
en: Men that have given their life for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.

la: insuper et excello fabrico sum in urbs Judas et fornicor facio habitator Hierusal et praevaricaris Judas
en: Moreover he built also high place in the city of Juda, and he made the inhabitant of Jerusalem to commit fornication, and Juda to transgress.

la: loquor sum Dominus ad Mosen dico
en: And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:

la: ubi non sum bos praesaepe vacuus sum ubi autem multus seges ibi manifestus fortitudo bos
en: Where there are no oxen, the crib is empty: but where there is much corn, there the strength of the ox is manifest.

la: Abram habito in terra Chanaan Loth moror sum in oppidum qui sum circa Jordanes et habito in Sodoma
en: Abram dwelt in the land of Chanaan; and Lot abode in the town that were about the Jordan, and dwelt in Sodom.

la: ecce hic omnis opero Deus tres vicis per singuli
en: Behold, all these thing God worketh three time within every one.

la: quis ego hic tribuo ut in infernus protego ego ut abscondo ego donec pertranseat furor tuus et constituo ego tempus in quo recordor meus
en: Who will grant me this, that thou mayst protect me in hell, and hide me till thy wrath pass, and appoint me a time when thou wilt remember me?

la: quare reputas sum ut iumentum et sordesco coram tu
en: Why are we reputed a beasts, and counted vile before you?

la: audio enim ille loquor lingua et magnifico Deum
en: For they heard them speaking with tongue and magnifying God.

la: persequor sum autem David ipse et quadringenti vir substiterant enim ducenti qui lassus transeo non possum torreo Besor
en: But David pursued, he and four hundred men: for two hundred stayed, who, being weary, could not go over the torrent Besor.

la: facio etiam atrium sacerdos et basilica grandis et ostium in basilica qui tego aer
en: He made also the court of the priests, and a great hall, and door in the hall, which he covered with brass.

la: et non sum subiectibilis ille et non ob-audio voco Domini Dei noster ut ambulo in mandatum is qui do nos
en: And we were not obedient to him, and we have not hearkened to the voice of the Lord our God, to walk in his commandment which he hath given us.

la: sed potis eo ad ovo qui pereo domus Israhel
en: But go ye rather to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.

la: qui vinco facio ille columna in templum Dei meus et foras non egredior amplus et scribo super is nomen Dei meus et nomen civitas Dei meus novus Hierusal qui descendo de caelum ab Deo meus et nomen meus novus
en: He that shall overcome, I will make him a pillar in the temple of my God: and he shall go out no more. And I will write upon him the name of my God and the name of the city of my God, the new Jerusalem, which cometh down out of heaven from my God, and my new name.

la: nunc ergo curo facio hic exemplum et do Ionathae et pono in mons sancio in locus celeber
en: Now, therefore, see that thou make a copy of these things, and let it be given to Jonathan, and set upon the holy mountain, in a conspicuous place.

la: et ego mitto promitto Patrae meus in tu tu autem sedeo in civitas quoadusque induo virtus ex altus
en: And I send the promise of my Father upon you: but stay you in the city till you be endued with power from on high.

la: scortum et vilis prostibulis non duco uxor neque is qui repudio sum ab marito quia consecro sum Deo suus
en: They shall not take to wife a harlot or a vile prostitute, nor one that ha been put away from her husband: because they are consecrated to their God,

la: vae Assur virga furor meus et baculus ipse in manus is indignatio meus
en: Woe to the Assyrian, he is the rod and the staff of my anger, and my indignation is in their hands.

la: Cuncta nosti, et scio quia non pro superbia et contumelia, et aliqui gloria cupiditas facio hoc, ut non adoro Aman superbissimum,
en: Thou knowest all things, and thou knowest that it wa not out of pride and or any desire of glory, that I refused to worship the proud Aman,

la: Quod ex alienus virtus sui adrogant, is ego ex meus non concedunt, scilicet quia imago non habeo et quia ego novo nobilitas est, quam certus pario bonus sum quam accipio corrupisse.
en: that which they lay claim to for themselves a a result of others merit they do not allow to me a the result of my own, no doubt because I have no ancestral image and because mine is a freshly minted nobility; yet surely it is better to have brought nobility into being than to have sullied it after it ha been inherited.

la: sed venio mitto tu ad Pharao ut educo populus meus filius Israhel de Aegyptus
en: But come, and I will send thee to Pharao, that thou mayst bring forth my people, the child of Israel, out of Egypt.

la: et contero superbia duritia vester do caelum tu desuper sicut ferrum et terra aeneus
en: And I will break the pride of your stubbornness: and I will make to you the heaven above a iron, and the earth a brass.

la: non grandis sum culpa cum quis furor sum furo enim ut ex-surio impleo anima
en: The fault is not so great when a man hath stolen: for he stealeth to fill his hungry soul:

la: Ingemuit Susanna, et ait: Angustiae sum ego undique: si enim hic egero, mors ego est: si autem non egero, non effugio manus vestras.
en: Susanna sighed, and said: I am straitened on every side: for if I do this thing, it is death to me: and if I do it not, I shall not escape your hands.

la: Dies argentum ex K. Nov. metior X olea lego facio qui loco est, et si emptor locarit, Idus solvito.
en: Date of payment: within ten month from the first of November he will pay the contract price for gathering and working up the olives, even if the purchaser ha made a contract, on the Ides.

la: et comprehendo civitas munio in terra Aegyptius et accipio spolium terra Aegyptius
en: And he took the strong city in the land of Egypt: and he took the spoil of the land of Egypt.

la: nonne succido sum erectio is et reliquiae is devoro ignis
en: Is not their exaltation cut down, and hath not fire devoured the remnant of them?

la: persequor sum autem is exercitus Chaldeorum et comprehendo Sedeciam in campus solitudo hiericuntinae et capio adduco ad Nabuchodonosor rex Babylon in Reblatha qui sum in terra Emath et loquor sum ad is iudicium
en: But the army of the Chaldeans pursued after them: and they took Sedecias in the plain of the desert of Jericho, and when they had taken him, they brought him to Nabuchodonosor king of Babylon to Reblatha, which is in the land of Emath: and he gave judgment upon him.

la: in caput turba clamito in foris portaris urbs profero verbum suus dico
en: At the head of multitude she crieth out, in the entrance of the gate of the city she uttereth her words, saying:

la: qui in multus experimentum tribulatio abundantia gaudium ipse et alo paupertas is abundo in divitiae simplicitas is
en: That in much experience of tribulation, they have had abundance of joy and their very deep poverty hath abounded unto the rich of their simplicity.

la: propter frigus piger araris nolo mendico ergo aestas et non do is
en: Because of the cold the sluggard would not plough: he shall beg therefore in the summer, and it shall not be given him.

la: Miamin Madia Belga
en: Miamin, Madia, Belga,

la: vir intellego loquor ego et vir sapio audio ego
en: Let men of understanding speak to me, and let a wise man hearken to me.

la: si autem non dimitto homo neque Pater vester dimitto pecco vester
en: But if you will not forgive men, neither will your Father forgive you your offences.

la: et testamentum nosco mediator Iesus et sanguis sparsio bonus loquor quam Abel
en: And to Jesus the mediator of the new testament, and to the sprinkling of blood which speaketh better than that of Abel.

la: et percutio omnis civitas munio et omnis urbs eligo et universus lignum fructifer succido cunctus fons aqua obturo et omnis ager egregius operio lapis
en: And you shall destroy every fenced city, and every choice city, and shall cut down every fruitful tree, and shall stop up all the spring of waters, and every goodly field you shall cover with stones.

la: et ad mortuus homo non ingredior ne polluo nisi ad pater et mater et filius et filia et frater et soror qui alter vir non habeo in qui contamino
en: And they shall come near no dead person, lest they be defiled, only their father and mother, and son and daughter, and brother and sister, that hath not had another husband: for whom they may become unclean.

la: atque expugno is idem dies percutio in os gladius omnis anima qui sum in is iuxta omnis qui facio Lachis
en: And took it the same day: and put to the sword all the soul that were in it, according to all that he had done to Lachis.

la: sol autem orior aestuo et quia non habeo radix a-ruo
en: And when the sun wa up they were scorched: and because they had not root, they withered away.

la: Iepthae quoque dico is si verus venio ad ego ut pugno pro tu contra filius Ammon trado is Dominus in manus meus ego sum princeps vester
en: Jephte also said to them: If you be come to me sincerely, that I should fight for you against the child of Ammon, and the Lord shall deliver them into my hand, shall I be your prince?

la: scio qui doceo tu praecipio atque justitia sicut mando ego Dominus Deus meus sic facio is in terra quam possessuri sum
en: You know that I have taught you statute and justices, a the Lord my God hath commanded me: so shall you do them in the land which you shall possess:

la: tollo igitur tu ex omnis esca qui mando possum et conporto apud tu et sum tam tu quam ille in cibus
en: Thou shalt take unto thee of all food that may be eaten, and thou shalt lay it up with thee: and it shall be food for thee and them.

la: qui si et frater non sum do hereditas frater pater is
en: And if he have no brethren, you shall give the inheritance to his father's brethren.

la: et do is ianitor domus in omnis ministerium is et universus qui fio in is
en: And I will make them doorkeeper of the house, for all the service thereof, and for all that shall be done therein.

la: et scio omnis populus terra quia Dominus ipse sum Deus et non sum ultra absque is
en: That all the people of the earth may know, that the Lord he is God, and there is no other besides him.

la: et si accedo ad ille nolo aliquis committo ne fors aufero vita tuus
en: And if thou come to him, commit no fault, lest he take away thy life.

la: habeo autem hic dies in monumentum et celebro is sollemnem Domino in generatio vester cultus sempiternus
en: And this day shall be for a memorial to you; and you shall keep it a feast to the Lord in your generations, with an everlasting observance.

la: et propter sanguis innoxius qui effundo et impleo Hierusal cruor innocens et ob hic res nolo Dominus propitiaris
en: And for the innocent blood that he shed, filling Jerusalem with innocent blood: and therefore the Lord would not be appeased.

la: Ozias autem gigno Ioatham Ioatham autem gigno Achaz Achaz autem gigno Ezechiam
en: And Ozias begot Joatham. And Joatham begot Achaz. And Achaz begot Ezechias.

la: cum autem tempus fructus appropinquo mitto servus suus ad agricola ut accipio fructus is
en: And when the time of the fruit drew nigh, he sent his servant to the husbandman that they might receive the fruit thereof.

la: sum igitur holocaustum multus adipes pacificus et libamen holocaustor et conpletus sum cultus domus Domini
en: So there were many holocausts, and the fat of peace offerings, and the libation of holocausts: and the service of the house of the Lord wa completed.

la: Ephraim ut video Tyrus sum fundo in pulchritudo et Ephraim educo ad interfector filius suus
en: Ephraim, a I saw, wa a Tyre, founded in beauty: and Ephraim shall bring out his child to the murderer.

la: ipse verus ad armentum curro et fero inde vitulis tener et bonus do puer qui festino et coquo ille
en: And he himself ran to the herd, and took from thence a calf very tender and very good, and gave it to a young man: who made haste and boiled it.

la: et Amorreos et Chananeos et Gergeseos et Iebuseos
en: And the Amorrhites, and the Chanaanits, and the Gergesites, and the Jebusites.

la: et relinquo ille iterum abeo et oro tertius idem sermo dico
en: And leaving them, he went again: and he prayed the third time, saying the selfsame word.

la: vel si gladius induco super terra ille et dico gladius transeo per terra et interfacio de is homo et jumentum
en: Or if I bring the sword upon that land, and say to the sword: Pass through the land: and I destroy man and beast out of it:

la: universus autem adoro Dominum dico ad is benedico tu Dominus in virtus suus quia per tu ad nihilis redigo inimicus noster
en: And they all adored the Lord, and said to her: The Lord hath blessed thee by his power, because by thee he hath brought our enemy to nought.

la: qui dico video nolo video et aspicio nolo aspicio nos is qui recta sum loquor nos placeo video nos error
en: Who say to the seers: See not: and to them that behold: Behold not for u those thing that are right: speak unto u pleasant things, see error for us.

la: Abrahae dico sum promissio et semen is non dico et semen quasi in multus sed quasi in unus et semen tuus qui sum Christus
en: To Abraham were the promise made and to his seed. He saith not: And to his seed a of many. But a of one: And to thy seed, which is Christ.

la: non inpediaris operaris semper et non veto usque ad mors iustificaris quoniam merces Dei maneo in aeternus
en: Let nothing hinder thee from praying always, and be not afraid to be justified even to death: for the reward of God continueth for ever.

la: divitiae addo amicus multus ab pauper autem et hic qui habeo separo
en: Riches make many friends: but from the poor man, even they whom he had, depart.

la: Si habeo aquam, vinum effluet, aqua manebit.
en: If it contains water, the wine will soak through and the water will remain,

la: filius Balae ancilla Rahelis Dan et Nepthalim
en: The son of Bala, Rachel's handmaid: Dan and Nephthali.

la: aegroto etiam Asum annus tricesimo nonus regnum suus dolor pes vehemens et neque in infirmitas suus quaero Dominum sed magis in medicus ars confido sum
en: And Asa fell sick in the nine and thirtieth year of his reign, of a most violent pain in his feet, and yet in his illness he did not seek the Lord, but rather trusted in the skill of physicians.

la: propter qui et ego ipse non sum dignus arbitror ut venio ad tu sed dico verbum et sano puer meus
en: For which cause neither did I think myself worthy to come to thee: but say the word, and my servant shall be healed.

la: statuo ergo ille omnis finis Judaea et tres civitas Lyddam et Ramathae qui addo sum Judaea ex Samaria et omnis confinis is sequestro omnis sacrifico in Hierosolyma pro hic qui ab is rex accipio per singuli annus et pro fructus terra et pomum
en: We have ratified, therefore, unto them all the border of Judea, and the three cities, Apherema, Lydda, and Ramatha, which are added to Judea, out of Samaria, and all their confines, to be set apart to all them that sacrifice in Jerusalem, instead of the payment which the king received of them every year, and for the fruit of the land, and of the trees.

la: CIV. Vinum familia per hiems qui utatur.
en: CIV. Wine for the hand to drink through the winter:

la: sed qui de ancilla secundus caro nascor sum qui autem de liber per repromissio
en: But he who wa of the bondwoman wa born according to the flesh: but he of the free woman wa by promise.

la: Haec utique non sine iniuria incolo accido potuerunt.
en: I hardly suppose these thing could have happened without hurt to the inhabitants.

la: cum porto claudeo in tenebrae et ille pariter exeo nescio quo abeo persequor cito et comprehendo is
en: And at the time of shutting the gate in the dark, they also went out together. I know not whither they are gone: pursue after them quickly, and you will overtake them.

la: numquid non sacrificium qui sacrifico in civitas Judas et in platea Hierusal tu et pater vester rex vester et princeps vester et populus terra hic recordor sum Dominus et ascendo super cor is
en: Was it not the sacrifice that you offered in the city of Juda, and in the street of Jerusalem, you and your fathers, your kings, and your princes, and the people of the land, which the Lord hath remembered, and hath it not entered into his heart?

la: venio autem ad ille mater et frater is et non possum adeo ad is prae turba
en: And his mother and brother came unto him: and they could not come at him for the crowd.

la: qui pater et ex qui Christus secundus caro qui sum super omnis Deus benedico in saeculum amen
en: Whose are the father and of whom is Christ, according to the flesh, who is over all things, God blessed for ever. Amen.

la: dico autem Dominus ad Mosen extendo manus tuus in caelum et sum tenebra super terra Aegyptius tam densus ut palparis queo
en: And the Lord said to Moses: Stretch out thy hand towards heaven: and may there be darkness upon the land of Egypt so thick that it may be felt.

la: frumentum ex omnis Syria in transeo suus paro constituo
en: He appointed corn to be prepared out of all Syria in his passage.

la: vesperus autem facio cum occido sol affero ad is omnis malus habeo et daemonium habeo
en: And when it wa evening, after sunset, they brought to him all that were ill and that were possessed with devils.

la: Domine Deus dominus meus Abraham occurro obsecro hodie ego et facio misericordia cum dominus meus Abraham
en: O Lord the God of my master Abraham, meet me today, I beseech thee, and show kindness to my master Abraham.

la: qui percutio pater suus et mater mors morior
en: He that striketh his father or mother, shall be put to death.

la: et cado in facies ante pes is gratia ago et hic sum Samaritanus
en: And he fell on his face before his feet, giving thanks. And this wa a Samaritan.

la: propter hic igitur causa rogo tu video et alloquor propter spes enim Israhel catena hic circumdo sum
en: For this cause therefore I desired to see you and to speak to you. Because that for the hope of Israel, I am bound with this chain.

la: Sed quo plenus et inpressius tam ipse quam dispositio is et voluntas adiremus, adiicio instrumentum litteraturae, si qui volo de deus inquirere, et inquisitus invenire, et invenio credere, et credo deservire.
en: But that more fully and more firmly we might approach God Himself and His thought and His will, He ha given u the help of books, that who will, may inquire regarding God, on inquiring may find Him, on finding Him may believe, on believing may serve Him.

la: Siquid emptor aut pastor aut pecus emptor dominus damnum dederit, vir bonus arbitratus resolvat.
en: All damage done to the owner by the renter or his herdsman or cattle shall be settled for according to the decision of an honest man;

la: dico is rex David nequaquam ita fio sed argentum do quantus valeo neque enim tu aufero debeo et sic offero Domino holocaustum gratuitus
en: And king David said to him: It shall not be so, but I will give thee money a much a it is worth: for I must not take it from thee, and so offer to the Lord holocaust free cost.

la: quoniam in praeceptum ipse placo fio et non sum minoratio in salus ille
en: For at his commandment favour is shewn, and there is no diminishing of his salvation.

la: dico sum senex ecce filius tuus Ioseph venio ad tu qui conforto sedeo in lectulus
en: And it wa told the old man: Behold thy son Joseph cometh to thee. And being strengthened, he sat on his bed.

la: circa undecimus verus exeo et invenio alius sto et dico ille quis hic stas totus dies otiosus
en: But about the eleventh hour he went out and found others standing, and he saith to them: Why stand you here all the day idle?

la: Ita compositum rebus, in locum quam magnus occulo discedit, atque post paulus cognosco Marius ex iter frumentas cum paucus cohors Sicca missum, qui oppidum primus omnis post malus pugna ab rex defecerat.
en: Having made these arrangements, the king withdrew to place a secluded a possible; and a little later he learned that Marius with a few cohort had been sent to fetch grain on a detour to Sicca, which wa the very first town to revolt from the king after his defeat in the battle.

la: propter qui dico surgo qui dormio et exsurgo ab morior et inlumino tu Christus
en: Wherefore he saith: Rise, thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead: and Christ shall enlighten thee.

la: ergo et ego facio in furor non parco oculus meus neque misereo et cum clamo ad auris meus vox magnus non exaudio is
en: Therefore I also will deal with them in my wrath: my eye shall not spare them, neither will I shew mercy: and when they shall cry to my ear with a loud voice, I will not hear them.

la: venio ergo vir Cariathiarim et duco arca Domini et infero is in domus Abinadab in Gabaa Eleazaris autem filius is sanctifico ut custodio arca Domini
en: And the men of Cariathiarim came, and fetched up the ark of the Lord, and carried it into the house of Abinadab, in Gabaa: and they sanctified Eleazar, his son, to keep the ark of the Lord.

la: et dico pater familia domus dico tu magister ubi sum diversorium ubi pascha cum discipulis meus manduco
en: And you shall say to the goodman of the house: The master saith to thee: Where is the guest chamber, where I may eat the pasch with my disciples?

la: et occaedes is et tertius dies resurgo et contristas sum vehemens
en: And they shall kill him, and the third day he shall rise again. And they were troubled exceedingly.

la: Onam autem habeo filius Semmei et Iada filius autem Semmei Nadab et Abisur
en: And Onam had son Semei, and Jada. And the son of Semei: Nadab, and Abisur.

la: Quoi Metellus peto mos rex ut sella iuxta poneret, item postea custodia causa turma eques Romanorum, uterque negaverat; honorem, qui is mos sum qui populus Romanus rex appellavisset, praesidium, qui contumeliosus in is foret, si eques Romanus satelles Numida tradererentur.
en: When Gauda asked Metellus to be allowed the kingly privilege of sitting on an official chair next to him and afterward for a squadron of Roman Knights to serve a a bodyguard, Metellus refused both requests: the honor on the ground that by custom it belonged only to those who had been formally recognized a king by the Romans; the guard, on the ground it would have been an insult to Roman Knights if they were handed over to a Numidian a his attendants.

la: post hic aspicio in visio nox et ecce bestia quartus terribilis atque mirabilis et fortis nimis dens ferreus habeo magnus co-medeor atque comminuo et reliquus pes suus conculco dissimilis autem sum ceterus bestia qui video ante is et habeo cornu decem
en: After this I beheld in the vision of the night, and lo, a fourth beast, terrible and wonderful, and exceeding strong, it had great iron teeth, eating and breaking in pieces, and treading down the rest with his feet: and it wa unlike to the other beast which I had seen before it, and had ten horns.

la: et Iersia et Helia et Zechri filius Ieroam
en: And Jersia, and Elia, and Zechri, the son of Jeroham.

la: et post dies sex ad-sumo Iesus Petrum et Iacobum et Iohannem frater is et duco ille in mons excello seorsus
en: And after six day Jesus taketh unto him Peter and James, and John his brother, and bringeth them up into a high mountain apart:

la: voluntas rex labium iustus qui recta loquor diligo
en: Just lip are the delight of kings: he that speaketh right thing shall be loved.

la: abominatio Domini omnis arrogo etiam si manus ad manus sum non sum innocens
en: Every proud man is an abomination to the Lord: though hand should be joined to hand, he is not innocent. The beginning of a good way is to do justice: and this is more acceptable with God, than to offer sacrifices.

la: qui vinco do is sedeo ego in thronus meus sicut et ego vinco et sedeo cum Patre meus in thronus is
en: To him that shall overcome, I will give to sit with me in my throne: a I also have overcome and am set down with my Father in his throne.

la: Postea stramentum circumdo alligatoque, ne gelus noceat.
en: Finally, wrap it in straw and bind tightly, to keep the cold from injuring it.

la: quicumque autem totus lex servo offendo autem in unus facio sum omnis reus
en: And whosoever shall keep the whole law, but offend in one point, is become guilty of all.

la: sed aqua quam do is fio in is fons aqua salio in vita aeternus
en: But the water that I will give him shall become in him a fountain of water, springing up into life everlasting.

la: arguo verbum is qui non sum aequalis tuus et loquor qui tu non expedio
en: Thou reprovest him by words, who is not equal to thee, and thou speakest that which is not good for thee.

la: et quidam Pharisaeus de turba dico ad ille magister increpo discipulus tuus
