en: And some of the Pharisees, from amongst the multitude, said to him: Master, rebuke thy disciples.

la: et revorto in terra suus cum ops multus et cor is adverro testamentum sancio et facio et revorto in terra suus
en: And he shall return into his land with much riches: and his heart shall be aginst the holy covenant, and he shall succeed, and shall return into his own land.

la: porro thalamus porta ad via oriental tres hinc et tres inde mensura unus tres et mensura unus frons ex uter pars
en: And the little chamber of the gate that looked eastward were three on this side, and three on that side: all three were of one measure, and the front of one measure, on both parts.

la: Quot adhuc tu repurgandae lateo leges, qui neque annus numerus neque conditor dignitas commendat, sed aequitas sola? et ideo cum iniquus recognoscuntur, mereo damnantur, licet damnent.
en: How many of your law lie forgotten, still to be reformed? What recommends a law is not the number of it year nor the dignity of it makers, but it equity and nothing else. So when law are recognized to be unjust, they are deservedly condemned, even if they do condemn.

la: ut in ipse experior Israhel utrum custodio via Domini et ambulo in is sicut custodio pater is an non
en: That through them I may try Israel, whether they will keep the way of the Lord, and walk in it, a their father kept it, or not.

la: sum autem qui manduco quinque mille vir
en: And they that did eat, were five thousand men.

la: ad qui respicio et quis sum fortitudo is
en: To whom doth he look, and who is his strength?

la: amen amen dico tu non possum Filius ab sui facio quisquam nisi qui video Patrem facio quicumque enim ille facio hic et Filius similis facio
en: Then Jesus answered and said to them: Amen, amen, I say unto you, the Son cannot do any thing of himself, but what he seeth the Father doing: for what thing soever he doth, these the Son also doth in like manner.

la: loquor ad filius Israhel et dico ad is vir qui uxor erro maritus contemno
en: Speak to the child of Israel, and thou shalt say to them: The man whose wife shall have gone astray, and contemning her husband,

la: et qui in sinister cornu sum video qui contero sum dexter cornu et sequor sum post Judas et qui cum ipse sum ab tergum
en: And they that were in the left wing saw that the right wing wa discomfited, and they followed after Judas, and them that were with him, at their back:

la: firmo igitur filius Ionadab filius Rechab praeceptum pater suus qui praecipio is populus autem iste non oboedio ego
en: So the son of Jonadab the son of Rechab have constantly kept the commandment of their father, which he commanded them: but this people hath not obeyed me.

la: et dico is discipulis unde ergo nos in desero panis tantus ut saturo turba tantus
en: And the disciple say unto him: Whence then should we have so many loaf in the desert, a to fill so great a multitude?

la: Locum ubi facies confodito. Postea amurca conspargo bene sino conbibat.
en: Turn the soil for the floor and pour amurca over it thickly, letting it soak in.

la: speculator Ephraim cum Deo meus propheta laqueus ruina super omnis via is insania in domus Dei is
en: The watchman of Ephraim wa with my God: the prophet is become a snare of ruin upon all his ways, madness is in the house of his God.

la: pro iustitia agoniaris pro anima tuus et usque ad mors certus pro iustitia et Deus expugno pro tu inimicus tuus
en: Strive for justice for thy soul, and even unto death fight for justice, and God will overthrow thy enemy for thee.

la: ecce Behemoth qui facio tu faenum quasi bos co-medeor
en: Behold behemoth whom I made with thee, he eateth grass like an ox.

la: quis habeo amplus homo de universus labor suus qui laboro sub sol
en: What hath a man more of all his labour, that he taketh under the sun?

la: novus autem et mater consummo sum
en: And last of all, after the sons, the mother also wa consumed.

la: quia hic dico Dominus insanabilis frango tuus malus plaga tuus
en: For thus saith the Lord: Thy bruise is incurable, thy wound is very grievous.

la: lingua autem nullus homo domaris possum inquietus malus plenus veneno mortifero
en: But the tongue no man can tame, an unquiet evil, full of deadly poison.

la: DELETH via Sion lugeo is qui non sum qui venio ad sollemnitas omnis porta is destruo sacerdos is gemo virgo is squalidus et ipse opprimo amaritudo
en: Daleth. The way of Sion mourn, because there are none that come to the solemn feast: all her gate are broken down; her priest sigh; her virgin are in affliction; and she is oppressed with bitterness.

la: Quam sum assiduus emineo fortuna comes invidia alo adhaereat, etiam hic colligo potest, qui cum Anicius Octaviique triumphus nemo interpellaret, fuere, qui Paulis impedio obniterentur.
en: How inseparable a companion of great success is jealousy, and how she attache herself to the most eminent, may be gathered from this fact: although no one raised objection to the triumph of Octavius and Anicius, there were those who tried to place obstacle in the way of that of Paulus.

la: Caesaris deinde et Messalla Corvinus consul debello apud Actium, ubi longus ante quam dimico exploro Iulianaris pars sum victoria.
en: Then, in the consulship of Caesar and Messala Corvinus,c the decisive battle took place at Actium. The victory of the Caesarian party wa a certainty long before the battle.

la: et hic sum vita humanus deceptio quoniam aut affectus aut rex deservio homo incommunicabilis nomen lapis et lignum in-pono
en: And this wa the occasion of deceiving human life: for men serving either their affection, or their kings, gave the incommunicable name to stone and wood.

la: amen dico tu quicumque dico hic mons tollo et mitto in mare et non haesito in cor suus sed credo quia quicumque dico fio fio is
en: Amen I say to you that whosoever shall say to this mountain, Be thou removed and be cast into the sea, and shall not stagger in his heart, but be believe that whatsoever he saith shall be done; it shall be done unto him.

la: induo tu arma Dei ut possum sto adverro insidiae diabolus
en: Put you on the armour of God, that you may be able to stand against the deceit of the devil.

la: dies tertius offertor vitulus undecim aries duo agnus anniculus immaculatus quattuordecim
en: The third day you shall offer eleven calves, two rams, and fourteen lamb of a year old, without blemish:

la: Si vinea ab vitis calvus erit, sulcus interpono ibi viveradicem serito, umbra ab sulcus removeo creber fodito.
en: If there are gap in the rows, run furrow and plant rooted cuttings, keep the furrow clear of shade, and cultivate frequently.

la: Recipite interim hic fabulam, similis sum vestris, dum ostendo quomodo Christus probo et qui penis tu eiusmodi fabula aemulo ad destructio veritas istiusmodi praeministraverint.
en: For the moment accept this story (it is like your own stories) while we show how Christ is proved, and who they were who, in order to destroy the truth, set about among you rival story of the same kind.

la: Dei perficio sum opus et omnis via is iudicium Deus fidelis et absque ullus iniquitas iustus et rectus
en: The work of God are perfect, and all his way are judgments: God is faithful and without any iniquity, he is just and right.

la: Consulatus tantummodo usque ad undecimus quin continuo Caesar, cum saepe obnitor repugnasset, impetro non potuit: nam dictatura quam pertinax is defero populus, tam consto repulit.
en: In the case of the consulship only, Caesar wa not able to have his way, but wa obliged to hold that office consecutively until the eleventh time in spite of his frequent effort to prevent it; but the dictatorship which the people persistently offered him, he a stubbornly refused.

la: hortus concludo soror meus sponsa hortus concludo fons signo
en: My sister, my spouse, is a garden enclosed, a garden enclosed, a fountain sealed up.

la: quia ecce ascendo in Hierosolyma et Filius homo trado princeps sacerdos et scribo et senex et damno is mors et trado is gens
en: Saying: Behold we go up to Jerusalem, and the Son of man shall be betrayed to the chief priest and to the scribe and ancients. And they shall condemn him to death and shall deliver him to the Gentiles.

la: filius Aradii cum exercitus tuus sum super murus tuus in circuitus sed et Pigmei qui sum in turris tuus faretras suus suspendo in murus tuus per gyrus ipse con-pleo pulchritudo tuus
en: The men of Arad were with thy army upon thy wall round about: the Pygmeans also that were in thy towers, hung up their quiver on thy wall round about: they perfected thy beauty.

la: et aio ingredior sum ad ego servus hebraeus qui adduco ut illudo ego
en: And said: The Hebrew servant, whom thou hast brought, came to me to abuse me.

la: Segetem ne defrudet: nam is infelix est.
en: He must not stint the seed for sowing, for that brings bad fortune.

la: respondeo autem dico ille qui habeo duo tunica do non habeo et qui habeo esca similis facio
en: And he answering, said to them: He that hath two coats, let him give to him that hath none; and he that hath meat, let him do in like manner.

la: et facio sum in dies Ahaz filius Ioatham filius Oziae rex Judas ascendo Rasin rex Syria et Phacee filius Romeliae rex Israhel in Hierusal ad proelio contra is et non possum debellaris is
en: And it came to pas in the day of Achaz the son of Joathan, the son of Ozias, king of Juda, that Rasin king of Syria and Phacee the son of Romelia king of Israel, came up to Jerusalem, to fight against it: but they could not prevail over it.

la: Incenatum jubeo esse.
en: Bid the patient refrain from eating in the evening,

la: Post victoriam'namque ascendo mons Tifata cum C. Norbanus concurrerat'Sulla gratus Dianae, qui numen regius ille sacro est, solvit; aqua salubritas medeor corpus nobilis ager omnis addico deae.
en: It wa while Sulla wa ascending Mount Tifata that he had encountered Gaius Norbanus. After his victory over him he paid a vow of gratitude to Diana, to whom that region is sacred, and consecrated to the goddess the water renowned for their salubrity and power to heal, a well a all the land in the vicinity.
